metadata.name: 𝚠𝚑𝚎𝚗 𝚖𝚢 𝚠𝚒𝚗𝚐𝚜 𝚋𝚕𝚘𝚘𝚖
metadata.description:
When my wings bloom, I'll spread them wide  
And take to the sky with all my might  
I'll leave behind the doubts and fears  
And rise above the pain and tears

I'll soar above the clouds so high  
And feel the wind rush through my wings  
I'll chase the sun and catch the stars  
And let my spirit sing

For when my wings are strong and free  
I'll finally be able to be  
The person I was meant to be  
With boundless potential, I'll see

The world in a new light, and know  
That anything is possible  
When my wings bloom, and I take flight  
My future will be bright.
